<TITLE> Businesses vow to help bereaved families </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, 1 Mar (bdnews24.com)  Top business leaders of the country have pledged financial assistance for the families who were bereaved in the BDR mutiny. "If necessary, the business community will support children who have lost parents, providing for their education and arranging future employment," said FBCCI president Annisul Huq on Sunday. BKMEA president Fazlul Huq said, "Exemplary punishment should be meted out to the ones responsible for this bloodbath to prevent the recurrence of such an event." The business leaders condemned the killings, at a press conference in the FBCCI auditorium, demanding a proper investigation into the tragic event and exemplary punishment for those responsible. "We want a neutral probe and its publication," said Annisul Huq. The head of the country's top business body also praised the government and prime minister for tackling the situation with effective measures. He also said the BDR rebellion would have no adverse impact on import-export activities or foreign investment in Bangladesh Former adviser Syed Manzur Elahi, ICC,B president Mahbubur Rahman and former FBCCI presidents Salman F Rahman and Mir Nasir Hossain were present at the briefing among others. bd
